claim.claim-text:
1. An interchangeable instrument system, comprising:
a plurality of separate instrument members each capable of assisting in a different phase of a medical procedure to be performed at an anatomical operative site;
a single instrument storage chamber for releasably receiving said instrument members accommodated in separate storage locations within said instrument storage chamber;
an instrument driver constructed and arranged for cooperative positioning relative to said instrument storage chamber, for selective coaxial alignment with one of said instrument members at a time, and for displacing said aligned instrument member from said instrument storage chamber toward said operative site; and
an indexing mechanism for positionally controlling at least one of said instrument driver and instrument storage chamber so as to provide relative displacement therebetween, whereby said indexing mechanism selectively and coaxially aligns said instrument driver with different ones of said instrument members.

22. An interchangeable instrument system, comprising:
a single instrument retainer having multiple storage locations for receiving a plurality of instruments disposed separately in said respective storage locations;
an instrument driver constructed and arranged for cooperative positioning relative to said instrument retainer, for selective coaxial alignment with one of said instruments at a time, and for displacing said aligned instrument from said instrument retainer toward an anatomical operative site;
an indexing mechanism controlling the position of said instrument retainer, whereby said indexing mechanism selectively and coaxially aligns different ones of said instruments with said instrument driver; and
an actuation member disposed at a user interface for controlling said indexing mechanism.
